#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
RFC notes -- modernize the RFC detail page, fix its page-break, and allow
editing your own notes (text + attachments).

Background: RFCDetails.js called a global GetNotes() that exists nowhere, which
threw inside _loadRFCData() and made init() bounce via handleError() -- i.e. the
RFC detail page failed to open. RFC notes were otherwise unimplemented on the
frontend (no render/save), while the backend (Note/GetRFCNotes, Note/SaveNote
with RFC=true upserting on NoteID, attachments via rfc=1) was intact.

Attachment model: the save proc replaces a note's attachment set with whatever
is passed (the frontend re-sends the set it wants to keep; a removed file is
simply omitted). There is no separate attachment-delete endpoint -- removal is
handled purely by what we send on save.

This change:
  NEW wwwroot/js/RFC/Features/RFCNotes.js   -- notes-thread controller. Reuses the
      shared Composer (input/char-count/attachments/drag-drop) and Format helpers.
      Loads Note/GetRFCNotes + note attachments (rfc=1), renders a thread of note
      cards, saves via Note/SaveNote (RFC=true) then re-fetches. RFC notes are a
      plain thread (no client/internal flag). EDIT OWN NOTES: each note carries
      notesUserID; on the current user's own already-saved notes an Edit pencil
      opens an inline editor -- textarea + an editable attachment row (remove an
      existing file via its chip x, attach more via the paperclip, max 5/10MB) +
      Save/Cancel (Esc cancels, Ctrl/Cmd+Enter saves). On save it sends the FULL
      desired attachment set (kept existing re-sent by their stored bytes + newly
      encoded files) with the existing NoteID, so the proc updates the text and
      replaces attachments to match. A plain text edit therefore preserves the
      note's files (they are re-sent), and removed files drop out.
  NEW wwwroot/css/Components/NoteThread.css -- self-contained styling for the note
      thread/cards/composer/attachment chips + the edit pencil, inline editor and
      its attachment row. Scoped under #Notes. Loaded on the RFC page only; the
      ticket page keeps its copy in TicketDetails.css (a possible future tidy-up).
  EDIT Views/Page/RFC/RFCDetails.cshtml    -- replaced the legacy #Notes markup
      (.Note-Div + the #NewNote-Button) with a modern thread + inline composer
      (rfc-* ids); removed the legacy _NotePanel include (the partial itself is
      kept -- TaskDetails.cshtml still uses it); loaded NoteThread.css + RFCNotes.js.
  EDIT wwwroot/js/RFC/Pages/RFCDetails.js  -- replaced the stray GetNotes(this.rfcId)
      call with RFCNotes.init(this.rfcId).

JS parses; no GetNotes references remain. The save/edit path is server-side and
untestable here (no server/DB): after deploy, exercise (1) adding an RFC note +
attachment, (2) editing your own note -- change text, remove an existing file,
add a new file -- and confirm the saved note matches (text updated, removed file
gone, new file present, untouched files retained), and (3) that the Edit control
only appears on your own notes. Ownership is gated client-side only; the proc
updates by NoteID, so server-side owner-enforcement would be a separate backend
hardening.
"""
